FBIS4-41916 "drsov125_f_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 National Affairs Prime Minister Cuts Cabinet Staff 20 Percent Prime Minister Cuts Cabinet Staff 20 Percent LD2906085394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1900 GMT 28 Jun 94 LD2906085394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] One of the first documents to be signed by Vitaliy Masol, the new prime minister of Ukraine, was a resolution on cutting the number of workers of the Cabinet office. In accordance with the resolution, the four structural subdivisions of the office administration have been abolished and the number of workers cut in a number of branches. the staff has been reduced by a total of 159 persons, that is, almost 20 percent.
